===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|thou|lang=enm}}, {{term|thow|lang=enm}}, {{term|thu|lang=enm}}, {{term|þou|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|þu|þū|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|þū|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|túh₂|lang=ine-pro}}. Akin to Old Frisian {{term|thu|thū|lang=ofs}} (West Frisian {{term|do|lang=fy}}), Old Saxon {{term|thu|thū|lang=osx}} (Low German {{term|du|lang=nds}}), Old Dutch {{term|thu|thū|lang=odt}} (Middle Dutch {{term|du|lang=dum}}, Limburgish {{term|doe|lang=li}}), Old High German {{term|du|dū|lang=goh}} (German {{term|du|lang=de}}), Old Norse {{term|þú|lang=non}}, (Icelandic {{term|þú|lang=is}}, Danish {{term|du|lang=da}}, Norwegian {{term|du|lang=no}}, Swedish {{term|du|lang=sv}}), Latin {{term|tu|lang=la}}, Ancient Greek {{term|σύ|tr=sý|lang=grc}} (Modern Greek {{term|εσύ|tr=esý}}).

